description: Latasha Renee  is with  Lamon Q Wiley  and  17 others . "The Tree That Stood Strong"  For years there was a tree in my Grandmother's front yard. That tree was a base when we played kickball, baseball, freezetag, and "it". We even had a basketball rim nailed to it and we played basketball at that very tree. I know that tree has been there 38+ years. The house has been there much longer so I'm sure that tree was older, if not as old as, my Grandmother. A strong tree grows from the root up. This family has grown from the root of Vester Lean Wright and Willie Wiley. When a tree reaches a certain point and has served its purpose, or bears no fruit or new leaves, it is often cut down. This tree has seen several seasons and has withstood the test of time. This tree was unshakeable, unbreakable, always maintaining its strength. The branches from this tree gave life to many other branches. These branches have yet given life to other branches where they can go out and grow strong just like the tree in the front yard "out ta da house", building firm, unshakeable foundations.  I learned today that that tree was just cut down about a month ago. And the stump was set on fire. Then I was told that the tree was still burning up until about 2 weeks ago. My Grandmother passed away a week ago. There was a scare not long before. The tree that has endured so much held on strong. It was not ready to go just yet. The tree took its time and finally decided to let nature take its course. When nature told the tree to rest it had no choice but to oblige.  To you, Grandma Vester and Big Daddy, rest well. For the branches that are the result of your strong foundation are doing well. The tree may be gone from the earth but its Spirit lives in each one of us. Until we meet again, I bid you farewell...  Tash
